reviews.text: Always a great time learning about CV history.

great place to visit with family .you can learn a lot about human culture  and  livelihood .
staffs were very friendly .They were conducting scavenger hunt that was super fun :)
its 1.5 hours from Minneapolis so you can plan for small road trip. :) :)
I love history and this place is local history at its best.
An interesting visit. Very detailed displays depicting this area of Wisconsin as it developed.
A spectacular museum for its size. Great place to learn about the history of Eau Claire and the Chippewa Valley! There is a huge farm life exhibit.
Very neat with a lot of information about the logging camps. Especially worth the visit and very cool when they have chainsaw carving contests from people all over the world.
I have to go back to get the full experience since we ran out of time. Mr. Mike did an AMAZING job with keeping 3rd graders interested.
Really neat place to visit lots of informative displays. Watch out for uneven sidewalls, fell and busted my hand badly.
Nice place to bring the family to enjoy the local history. The area has playgrounds and sports if the history needs a break.

Great exhibits for all ages. Clean, well maintained. Very helpful volunteers. Really well done and a great example for smaller cities in how to do a museum well.

The Paul Bunyan theme wasn't really necessary, but it's probably fun for kids.
Local bar that has a friendly atmosphere. Paired with the cheap drinks and great food, this place is a must stop for anything from watching sports to a chill weekday night.
Top notch. Very small menu but everything on it is amazing.

Always the best place in EC. Diverse crowd, cool bartenders, simple food, low key atmosphere. IveI got a 20+ year history of "whenever I'm in town, gotta stop at Ray's"... It's iconic and never disappoints!
Great hot beefs & soups, great beer and super service!

Simple bar with good cheap drinks. Often a fun friendly atmosphere.  I always get a hot beef sandwich when I'm there, they are delicious. They also make a horseradish mustard from scratch. Sometimes I go just to buy some mustard for my personal use at home. I've heard they're Spanish stew idea great also, but haven't tried it yet myself.

Whenever I am visiting Eau Claire I always go here for a coffee. They do  sell one the best coffee in the town. They have a big seating place and its fairly busy during the morning/afternoon. The employees are friendly and nice. They sell sandwiches, soup, cookies and muffins. I just wished they had more variety of breakfast menu though. But beside that its a good place to chill.

Nice, comfortable atmosphere. I've only been in there a couple times now, today. I can make this a place to visit regularly in my sobriety. Gotta thank them for their hospitality, as I am a southern American American. Would highly recommend it to my friends.
Great local music venue with good coffee and food. Their pita sandwiches and soup are the best.

What a fun place. I stopped by for a coffee,  I decided to treat myself to something special. The girls at the counter were friendly and helpful. I had a peppermint mocha which was delicious. I will be back.
Best sandwiches ever! So delicious. Great quiche and is the only place I'll drink coffee besides Starbucks which is saying ALOT! I absolutely love this place.
A tasty treat that's not too shabby at all. Better then most breakfast/lunch places around here fo sho! Make sure to check out the Lonesome Fowl and ADD BACON! :D

Excellent place for breakfast and coffee in a cozy cafe.  The staff is friendly and quickly get you your drinks and food.  During the weekend mornings, the place is very busy and seating is tight but well worth it.

Owner exhibited a prime example of "age discrimination" in "putting on hold" (owners words) of a senior citizen server.  Effectively replaced with newer younger models with no reason given.  Disgusting behavior by a business owner who should be ashamed of her actions in such a wonderful, diverse community. Discrimination of any kind  has NO place in Eau Claire. Just be mindful that any patronage of this place is support of such behavior.
Delicious food. Friendly staff and cute decor. Try the quiche, it is wonderful.
Great place for breakfast or lunch. Such a variety to choose from and everything that I have ever had is very good.

Nice place. So many types of beer. The food is delicious and different than the norm. We watched a local band called Filthy Sweet and the show was good. The service was excellent and the beer was as well. They give you free samples of the different beer so you will know what to order. I recommend the stuffed mushroom cap. It was very good.
Had a super good time. We all will be back. Super good bar tenders. Good food and beer.
Try the Filthy Sweet Blueberry Wheat ale. Delicious! Very friendly staff and good pizza. Awesome live music by Filthy Sweet.

Amazing place, super cool staff, and the Filthy Sweet Blueberry wheat is amazing!!
Fantastic job guys!! I'll be back for sure.

S.. L.. O.. W.. service. Food is okay, but it's quite cool/cold by the time you get it. Ordering at the bar idea is meh - noticed some bartenders ignore patrons approaching the bar. Three different types of their own beers that our group initially ordered were out. That's great if you're so popular that you run out of beer....but you ARE a brewery, so that kind of seems ironic. 
Tipping is weird because you pay before you receive your food/service- I felt guilty doing less than a 20% tip because I didn't want to come off as a cheapskate, but then afterwards, I kind of wish I got about half of that back. I'm a former waitress, so I know how grueling it can be, but to drop off food and pick up plates (no check backs, drink refills, follow-ups in between) no, I'm sorry, it wasn't worth the 20%. $70 for 3 burger-type meals & 2 kids meals + 3 beers. Yikes! 

Not sure if they are slow because of low staff, few kitchen cooks/help, or because the staff has to wander around to search for the table they are looking for to deliver food. I REALLY was excited to come here and I REALLY wanted to like it, but it's just more of a hangout, drink beer, and stand around kind of place. Which is great if that's what you're out for, but we were on an 'out to dinner' trip and this isn't the place unless you want to sit and wait...and wait...and wait.. our total time here was 2 hours - just to get dinner.

This is by far the best restaurant in town! Friendly and responsive staff along with a soothing atmosphere! My girlfriend and I have come here a few times and always had an amazing experience. I would recommend the Salmon when you come here. Always made perfectly!

Amazing! My wife and I went here together for the first time and everything was absolutely delicious. Prices were a little high, but definitely worth it. Highly recommend checking this place out and I'm certain that we will be back again in the future!

Stopped on down to Mona Lisa's for a birthday dinner. The ambiance was classy but casual. The service was top notch.  The menu had a little bit of everything to offer. My friend and I got an appetizer and entree and desert, and hands down it was one of the best restaurant's I've been to. For the quality of food and service the price is well worth it.

As a business owner to another business, I would have to say I was disappointed in how we were treated. It should not matter what background, ethnicity or color you are. It doesnt matter if I wear a white coat, a suit or if I had holes in my shoes. People come to a great place to be treated better, to be served better, to try better things. Try taking in a little of my advice and remember that your actions reflect on your business. Thank you and have a great day.
Love this little gem! Just sat at the bar this time as I was alone.  Still great experience and really great food
Still one of the best pizzas in eau Claire. Great service. Over looked staple in the area. There is reason they are still in business when. So many other places have come and gone

Food and service was good. Really loved the hospitality from the owner/manager. She came up to our table several times to see how we were doing, even provided us with more warm bread. The waitress was attentive, but the first basket of bread that she gave us wasn’t warmed up.

Chicken Alfredo is much much too oily, made me sick. Tasted much worse than my first batch of trying to make my own chicken Alfredo. For 50+ bucks for a meal for 2 (no drinks even) expect it to be half way decent. Olive garden is 15x better at same price.... Save you money and Olive garden it up.

Best Italian food around!!!! Wife and I came for the first time and they didn’t let us down one bit! Owner even made time to come over and give us the history of the restaurant and just made the whole experience great! Thanks again and will definitely be coming back to visit!!!!!

It was amazing our first experience an we went tonight to celebrate Valentine's day we were very pleased with everything an even got to run into the owner. she seemed very nice an even gave me a nice hug we will definitely be coming back an will put the word out to others looking for a really good place to eat waitress was awesome as well kept coming back just to make sure we were doing okay u guys are awesome 😀

My dad and his girlfriend had came up from Indiana for a Visit and Mike's Smokehouse was suggested for a place to eat at. I had not been there in years. It has changed so much since I was there last. I didn't get the BBQ, Being it was a Friday I had gotten the Fish Fry and I will tell you I was amazed. The prices were Pretty good. You got a lot of food for your money. I had to give some of my food to my girls because there was so much. The Fish Was Excellent.
I loved the Western Theme going on. My dad's Girlfriend had to take pictures of the inside. Yes it was a nice place.
Customer Service, What can I say. They had some really friendly waitresses. I loved their Southern type charm. "Even though we are located in the Northern part of the United States."  I had to use Southern Charm as an example.
I would recommend Mike's Smokehouse if you are wanting a good Fish Fry on a Friday Night.
No Long Wait time either.
:)
Awesome service!  Awesome food!  Awesome prices!  Great value.... If you are near Eau Claire you should go there!

I'm a local.  Haven't gone here in years (Famous Dave's is a favorite of a couple we go out to eat with, so we go there).  Came across a gift certificate for a sandwich that I had won on a radio station quite awhile ago, but noticed it didn't have an expiration date on it... so figured I give them a try.
Went out of my way to stop there for lunch - they told me at front counter that certificate wasn't good.  Current ones have a stamp on it.  I told them it was older, but I definitely won it, I wasn't tring to scam them.  They recommended I drive to the radio station to have them exchange it.  I told them I was extremely disappointed and I wouldn't be back.
Let a customer leave angry over what was probably $1 in food cost to them????
No wonder our friends goto Famous Dave's.
This is the perfect place for you if you like: tangy watery bbq sauce, dry meat, and no free soda refills. Dont waste your money.  I have given them 2 chances, still the same place.
That is not authentic bbq, brisket had no fat cap and no bark, chicken was bland, and the ribs were just ok. No smoke flavornfelt like I was eating canned chicken and lunch meat

After getting to know them better, I eat at least once per month at Tokyo Japanese Restaurant. The service is absolutely impecable, the food is great, and the quality is constant. You never get bad sushi, bad soup, or soggy tempura. The awesome fish selection, availability of Japanese beverages and the care and dedication towards the food and the customer makes me want to go there again and again.

I've been visiting this restaurant every once in a while for years. Today the service and quality of the food were amazing, as always (I didn't realize I hadn't left a review until now). 

This is one of the (unfortunately) very rare places I know of in Cluj where I am confident I won't be let down when I return, and that's why I prefer Tokyo over other places for special moments.

I've become more and more appreciative of places that are able to offer the same great food and service constantly, irrespective of the time of year or how busy the restaurant is. 

I've been to Tokyo on quiet afternoons or on days when every table was booked and I noticed no difference in the experience - and that's just one of the things I love about this restaurant.

The food tastes amazing, in particular the seafood is well prepared and always fresh, and you can have sakuramochi for desert! 

The menu is varied and can offer a great experience of Japanese cuisine. It's even possible to order dishes consisting of smaller portions of various entrees and deserts, a really nice idea for those of us who have a hard time deciding what to order.

The staff are always ready to offer a smile and good advice, and they seem to know everything there is to know about the menu.

The atmosphere is intimate and quiet, with airy rooms that take your mind off the cluttered city, and the music is soothing and not too loud. I've noticed people tend to speak in hushed tones, and that can be a welcome change from the usual types of places where you need to raise your voice over the music and over the voices of people at other tables, but you do need to be in the mood for it.

There is more I could say about Tokyo, but it's probably better to visit them and discover for yourselves a place that strives to offer perfection in the smallest details, and, at least in my opinion, achieves it.

Thank you for a wonderful evening and for the care and attention to details you always spoil us with.

It was my first time for my friends and me in this restaurant. The service is amazing. You are being greeted by everyone with a nice smile. The woman at the reception kindly took our luggages and kept for the time being there.
The waitress was also very polite and helped us with the menu. She also knew what dishes were vegan and/or gluten-free. 
The food was very very good and we didn't wait so long for it.
If I am ever going back to Cluj, I will definitely go back to this restaurant!

Awesome food and service. The person who served us was very nice and hospitable.
I find the design of the restaurant quite boring.

Taste and quality of the Sushi was really nice. The service very welcoming and discrete.
Only thing I would recommend is to improve the presentation and arrangement of the food
Excellent coffee shop! Perfect place to work or relax. Great food and drink options. Great people. Great environment :)

Quaint little local coffee shop.  Haven't gone here to
 much so I cannot say to much about the coffee or service. My gf loves going here and says it is always good. Says it is the best coffee in eau claire.
I've never visited such a lively coffee shop. If I wasn't from a school 3.5 hours away, I would be here everyday! I can't wait to visit Eau Claire again to visit this coffee house!

We got a double espresso and a  cappuccino.

The coffee in both tasted burnt and the foam on my cappuccino went halfway down the cup. 

The service and atmosphere was good, but the price was too much for a not top notch quality product. For the owners reference I was here on a Monday before noon.

The seating is a bit tight, but the Goat always manages to feel like home. Their coffee always has a filling, warm, feel to it, and their food is very savory. While no particular item on their menu is to die for, you will never go wrong by choosing to go to the Goat.

I'm a Caribou coffee person myself, but it was half-price day so I thought I would give it a go. Espresso there is too on the bitter side for my liking, I prefer a richer flavor. But the staff was nice, and I got what I asked for, regardless my own taste buds...
They always treat me with respect talk to me like a human and they are amazing making coffees
Awesome when I'm spending almost $6 for a coffee and don't get what I order. Guess I'll drive the extra distance to go to the other location. At least I know they'll give me what I order .
Great coffee great place like the remodel. It’s what u expect
Tis a starbucks, ya can't go wrong

Whenever I am visiting Eau Claire I always go here for a coffee. They do  sell one the best coffee in the town. They have a big seating place and its fairly busy during the morning/afternoon. The employees are friendly and nice. They sell sandwiches, soup, cookies and muffins. I just wished they had more variety of breakfast menu though. But beside that its a good place to chill.

Nice, comfortable atmosphere. I've only been in there a couple times now, today. I can make this a place to visit regularly in my sobriety. Gotta thank them for their hospitality, as I am a southern American American. Would highly recommend it to my friends.
Great local music venue with good coffee and food. Their pita sandwiches and soup are the best.

What a fun place. I stopped by for a coffee,  I decided to treat myself to something special. The girls at the counter were friendly and helpful. I had a peppermint mocha which was delicious. I will be back.
Best sandwiches ever! So delicious. Great quiche and is the only place I'll drink coffee besides Starbucks which is saying ALOT! I absolutely love this place.
